495 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE q31_t clip_q63_to_q31(
496 q63_t x)
497 {
498 return ((q31_t) (x >> 32) != ((q31_t) x >> 31)) ?
499 ((0x7FFFFFFF ^ ((q31_t) (x >> 63)))) : (q31_t) x;
500 }
501
505 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE q15_t clip_q63_to_q15(
506 q63_t x)
507 {
508 return ((q31_t) (x >> 32) != ((q31_t) x >> 31)) ?
509 ((0x7FFF ^ ((q15_t) (x >> 63)))) : (q15_t) (x >> 15);
510 }
511
515 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE q7_t clip_q31_to_q7(
516 q31_t x)
517 {
518 return ((q31_t) (x >> 24) != ((q31_t) x >> 23)) ?
519 ((0x7F ^ ((q7_t) (x >> 31)))) : (q7_t) x;
520 }
521
525 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE q15_t clip_q31_to_q15(
526 q31_t x)
527 {
528 return ((q31_t) (x >> 16) != ((q31_t) x >> 15)) ?
529 ((0x7FFF ^ ((q15_t) (x >> 31)))) : (q15_t) x;
530 }

537 q63_t x,

539 {
540 return ((((q63_t) (x & 0x00000000FFFFFFFF) * y) >> 32) +

552 q31_t data);

554 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE uint32_t __CLZ(
555 q31_t data)
556 {
557 uint32_t count = 0;
558 uint32_t mask = 0x80000000;
559
560 while((data & mask) == 0)
561 {
562 count += 1u;
563 mask = mask >> 1u;
564 }
565
566 return (count);
567 }

574 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE uint32_t arm_recip_q31(
575 q31_t in,
576 q31_t * dst,
577 q31_t * pRecipTable)
578 {
579 q31_t out;
580 uint32_t tempVal;
581 uint32_t index, i;
582 uint32_t signBits;
583
584 if(in > 0)
585 {
586 signBits = ((uint32_t) (__CLZ( in) - 1));
587 }
588 else
589 {
590 signBits = ((uint32_t) (__CLZ(-in) - 1));
591 }
592
593 /* Convert input sample to 1.31 format */
594 in = (in << signBits);
595
596 /* calculation of index for initial approximated Val */
597 index = (uint32_t)(in >> 24);
598 index = (index & INDEX_MASK);
599
600 /* 1.31 with exp 1 */
601 out = pRecipTable[index];
602
603 /* calculation of reciprocal value */
604 /* running approximation for two iterations */
605 for (i = 0u; i < 2u; i++)
606 {
607 tempVal = (uint32_t) (((q63_t) in * out) >> 31);
608 tempVal = 0x7FFFFFFFu - tempVal;
609 /* 1.31 with exp 1 */
610 /* out = (q31_t) (((q63_t) out * tempVal) >> 30); */
611 out = clip_q63_to_q31(((q63_t) out * tempVal) >> 30);
612 }
613
614 /* write output */
615 *dst = out;
616
617 /* return num of signbits of out = 1/in value */
618 return (signBits + 1u);
619 }

621
625 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE uint32_t arm_recip_q15(
626 q15_t in,
627 q15_t * dst,
628 q15_t * pRecipTable)
629 {
630 q15_t out = 0;
631 uint32_t tempVal = 0;
632 uint32_t index = 0, i = 0;
633 uint32_t signBits = 0;
634
635 if(in > 0)
636 {
637 signBits = ((uint32_t)(__CLZ( in) - 17));
638 }
639 else
640 {
641 signBits = ((uint32_t)(__CLZ(-in) - 17));
642 }
643
644 /* Convert input sample to 1.15 format */
645 in = (in << signBits);
646
647 /* calculation of index for initial approximated Val */
648 index = (uint32_t)(in >> 8);
649 index = (index & INDEX_MASK);
650
651 /* 1.15 with exp 1 */
652 out = pRecipTable[index];
653
654 /* calculation of reciprocal value */
655 /* running approximation for two iterations */
656 for (i = 0u; i < 2u; i++)
657 {
658 tempVal = (uint32_t) (((q31_t) in * out) >> 15);
659 tempVal = 0x7FFFu - tempVal;
660 /* 1.15 with exp 1 */
661 out = (q15_t) (((q31_t) out * tempVal) >> 14);
662 /* out = clip_q31_to_q15(((q31_t) out * tempVal) >> 14); */
663 }
664
665 /* write output */
666 *dst = out;
667
668 /* return num of signbits of out = 1/in value */
669 return (signBits + 1);
670 }

675 */
676#if defined(ARM_MATH_CM0_FAMILY)
677 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE q31_t __SSAT(
678 q31_t x,
679 uint32_t y)
680 {
681 int32_t posMax, negMin;
682 uint32_t i;
683
684 posMax = 1;
685 for (i = 0; i < (y - 1); i++)
686 {
687 posMax = posMax * 2;
688 }
689
690 if(x > 0)
691 {
692 posMax = (posMax - 1);
693
694 if(x > posMax)
695 {
696 x = posMax;
697 }
698 }
699 else
700 {
701 negMin = -posMax;
702
703 if(x < negMin)
704 {
705 x = negMin;
706 }
707 }
708 return (x);
709 }
710#endif /* end of ARM_MATH_CM0_FAMILY */

718 /*
719 * @brief C custom defined QADD8 for M3 and M0 processors
720 */
721 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE uint32_t __QADD8(
722 uint32_t x,
723 uint32_t y)
724 {
725 q31_t r, s, t, u;
726
727 r = __SSAT(((((q31_t)x << 24) >> 24) + (((q31_t)y << 24) >> 24)), 8) & (int32_t)0x000000FF;
728 s = __SSAT(((((q31_t)x << 16) >> 24) + (((q31_t)y << 16) >> 24)), 8) & (int32_t)0x000000FF;
729 t = __SSAT(((((q31_t)x << 8) >> 24) + (((q31_t)y << 8) >> 24)), 8) & (int32_t)0x000000FF;
730 u = __SSAT(((((q31_t)x ) >> 24) + (((q31_t)y ) >> 24)), 8) & (int32_t)0x000000FF;
731
732 return ((uint32_t)((u << 24) | (t << 16) | (s << 8) | (r )));
733 }

739 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE uint32_t __QSUB8(

746 s = __SSAT(((((q31_t)x << 16) >> 24) - (((q31_t)y << 16) >> 24)), 8) & (int32_t)0x000000FF;
747 t = __SSAT(((((q31_t)x << 8) >> 24) - (((q31_t)y << 8) >> 24)), 8) & (int32_t)0x000000FF;
748 u = __SSAT(((((q31_t)x ) >> 24) - (((q31_t)y ) >> 24)), 8) & (int32_t)0x000000FF;
749
750 return ((uint32_t)((u << 24) | (t << 16) | (s << 8) | (r )));
751 }

4810
4817 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE float32_t arm_pid_f32(
4818 arm_pid_instance_f32 * S,
4819 float32_t in)
4820 {
4821 float32_t out;
4822
4823 /* y[n] = y[n-1] + A0 * x[n] + A1 * x[n-1] + A2 * x[n-2] */
4824 out = (S->A0 * in) +
4825 (S->A1 * S->state[0]) + (S->A2 * S->state[1]) + (S->state[2]);
4826
4827 /* Update state */
4828 S->state[1] = S->state[0];
4829 S->state[0] = in;
4830 S->state[2] = out;
4831
4832 /* return to application */
4833 return (out);
4834
4835 }
4836
4851 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE q31_t arm_pid_q31(
4852 arm_pid_instance_q31 * S,
4853 q31_t in)
4854 {
4855 q63_t acc;
4856 q31_t out;
4857
4858 /* acc = A0 * x[n] */
4859 acc = (q63_t) S->A0 * in;
4860
4861 /* acc += A1 * x[n-1] */
4862 acc += (q63_t) S->A1 * S->state[0];
4863
4864 /* acc += A2 * x[n-2] */
4865 acc += (q63_t) S->A2 * S->state[1];
4866
4867 /* convert output to 1.31 format to add y[n-1] */
4868 out = (q31_t) (acc >> 31u);
4869
4870 /* out += y[n-1] */
4871 out += S->state[2];
4872
4873 /* Update state */
4874 S->state[1] = S->state[0];
4875 S->state[0] = in;
4876 S->state[2] = out;
4877
4878 /* return to application */
4879 return (out);
4880 }
4881
4882
4898 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE q15_t arm_pid_q15(
4899 arm_pid_instance_q15 * S,
4900 q15_t in)
4901 {
4902 q63_t acc;
4903 q15_t out;
4904
4905#ifndef ARM_MATH_CM0_FAMILY
4906 __SIMD32_TYPE *vstate;
4907
4908 /* Implementation of PID controller */
4909
4910 /* acc = A0 * x[n] */
4911 acc = (q31_t) __SMUAD((uint32_t)S->A0, (uint32_t)in);
4912
4913 /* acc += A1 * x[n-1] + A2 * x[n-2] */
4914 vstate = __SIMD32_CONST(S->state);
4915 acc = (q63_t)__SMLALD((uint32_t)S->A1, (uint32_t)*vstate, (uint64_t)acc);
4916#else
4917 /* acc = A0 * x[n] */
4918 acc = ((q31_t) S->A0) * in;
4919
4920 /* acc += A1 * x[n-1] + A2 * x[n-2] */
4921 acc += (q31_t) S->A1 * S->state[0];
4922 acc += (q31_t) S->A2 * S->state[1];
4923#endif
4924
4925 /* acc += y[n-1] */
4926 acc += (q31_t) S->state[2] << 15;
4927
4928 /* saturate the output */
4929 out = (q15_t) (__SSAT((acc >> 15), 16));
4930
4931 /* Update state */
4932 S->state[1] = S->state[0];
4933 S->state[0] = in;
4934 S->state[2] = out;
4935
4936 /* return to application */
4937 return (out);
4938 }

5037 q31_t Ia,
5038 q31_t Ib,
5039 q31_t * pIalpha,
5040 q31_t * pIbeta)
5041 {
5042 q31_t product1, product2; /* Temporary variables used to store intermediate results */
5043
5044 /* Calculating pIalpha from Ia by equation pIalpha = Ia */
5045 *pIalpha = Ia;
5046

5051 product2 = (q31_t) (((q63_t) Ib * 0x49E69D16) >> 30);

5054 *pIbeta = __QADD(product1, product2);

5455 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE float32_t arm_linear_interp_f32(
5456 arm_linear_interp_instance_f32 * S,
5457 float32_t x)
5458 {
5459 float32_t y;
5460 float32_t x0, x1; /* Nearest input values */
5461 float32_t y0, y1; /* Nearest output values */
5462 float32_t xSpacing = S->xSpacing; /* spacing between input values */
5463 int32_t i; /* Index variable */
5464 float32_t *pYData = S->pYData; /* pointer to output table */
5465
5466 /* Calculation of index */
5467 i = (int32_t) ((x - S->x1) / xSpacing);
5468
5469 if(i < 0)
5470 {
5471 /* Iniatilize output for below specified range as least output value of table */
5472 y = pYData[0];
5473 }
5474 else if((uint32_t)i >= S->nValues)
5475 {
5476 /* Iniatilize output for above specified range as last output value of table */
5477 y = pYData[S->nValues - 1];
5478 }
5479 else
5480 {
5481 /* Calculation of nearest input values */
5482 x0 = S->x1 + i * xSpacing;
5483 x1 = S->x1 + (i + 1) * xSpacing;
5484
5485 /* Read of nearest output values */
5486 y0 = pYData[i];
5487 y1 = pYData[i + 1];
5488
5489 /* Calculation of output */
5490 y = y0 + (x - x0) * ((y1 - y0) / (x1 - x0));
5491
5492 }
5493
5494 /* returns output value */
5495 return (y);
5496 }

5512 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE q31_t arm_linear_interp_q31(
5513 q31_t * pYData,
5514 q31_t x,
5515 uint32_t nValues)
5516 {
5517 q31_t y; /* output */
5518 q31_t y0, y1; /* Nearest output values */
5519 q31_t fract; /* fractional part */
5520 int32_t index; /* Index to read nearest output values */
5521
5522 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
5523 /* 12 bits for the table index */
5524 /* Index value calculation */
5525 index = ((x & (q31_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
5526
5527 if(index >= (int32_t)(nValues - 1))
5528 {
5529 return (pYData[nValues - 1]);
5530 }
5531 else if(index < 0)
5532 {
5533 return (pYData[0]);
5534 }
5535 else
5536 {
5537 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
5538 /* shift left by 11 to keep fract in 1.31 format */
5539 fract = (x & 0x000FFFFF) << 11;
5540
5541 /* Read two nearest output values from the index in 1.31(q31) format */
5542 y0 = pYData[index];
5543 y1 = pYData[index + 1];
5544
5545 /* Calculation of y0 * (1-fract) and y is in 2.30 format */
5546 y = ((q31_t) ((q63_t) y0 * (0x7FFFFFFF - fract) >> 32));
5547
5548 /* Calculation of y0 * (1-fract) + y1 *fract and y is in 2.30 format */
5549 y += ((q31_t) (((q63_t) y1 * fract) >> 32));
5550
5551 /* Convert y to 1.31 format */
5552 return (y << 1u);
5553 }
5554 }

5570 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE q15_t arm_linear_interp_q15(
5571 q15_t * pYData,
5572 q31_t x,
5573 uint32_t nValues)
5574 {
5575 q63_t y; /* output */
5576 q15_t y0, y1; /* Nearest output values */
5577 q31_t fract; /* fractional part */
5578 int32_t index; /* Index to read nearest output values */
5579
5580 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
5581 /* 12 bits for the table index */
5582 /* Index value calculation */
5583 index = ((x & (int32_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
5584
5585 if(index >= (int32_t)(nValues - 1))
5586 {
5587 return (pYData[nValues - 1]);
5588 }
5589 else if(index < 0)
5590 {
5591 return (pYData[0]);
5592 }
5593 else
5594 {
5595 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
5596 /* fract is in 12.20 format */
5597 fract = (x & 0x000FFFFF);
5598
5599 /* Read two nearest output values from the index */
5600 y0 = pYData[index];
5601 y1 = pYData[index + 1];
5602
5603 /* Calculation of y0 * (1-fract) and y is in 13.35 format */
5604 y = ((q63_t) y0 * (0xFFFFF - fract));
5605
5606 /* Calculation of (y0 * (1-fract) + y1 * fract) and y is in 13.35 format */
5607 y += ((q63_t) y1 * (fract));
5608
5609 /* convert y to 1.15 format */
5610 return (q15_t) (y >> 20);
5611 }

5627 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE q7_t arm_linear_interp_q7(
5628 q7_t * pYData,
5629 q31_t x,
5630 uint32_t nValues)
5631 {
5632 q31_t y; /* output */
5633 q7_t y0, y1; /* Nearest output values */
5634 q31_t fract; /* fractional part */
5635 uint32_t index; /* Index to read nearest output values */
5636
5637 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
5638 /* 12 bits for the table index */
5639 /* Index value calculation */
5640 if (x < 0)
5641 {
5642 return (pYData[0]);
5643 }
5644 index = (x >> 20) & 0xfff;
5645
5646 if(index >= (nValues - 1))
5647 {
5648 return (pYData[nValues - 1]);
5649 }
5650 else
5651 {
5652 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
5653 /* fract is in 12.20 format */
5654 fract = (x & 0x000FFFFF);
5655
5656 /* Read two nearest output values from the index and are in 1.7(q7) format */
5657 y0 = pYData[index];
5658 y1 = pYData[index + 1];
5659
5660 /* Calculation of y0 * (1-fract ) and y is in 13.27(q27) format */
5661 y = ((y0 * (0xFFFFF - fract)));
5662
5663 /* Calculation of y1 * fract + y0 * (1-fract) and y is in 13.27(q27) format */
5664 y += (y1 * fract);
5665
5666 /* convert y to 1.7(q7) format */
5667 return (q7_t) (y >> 20);

5827 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE void arm_circularWrite_f32(
5828 int32_t * circBuffer,
5829 int32_t L,
5830 uint16_t * writeOffset,
5831 int32_t bufferInc,
5832 const int32_t * src,
5833 int32_t srcInc,
5834 uint32_t blockSize)
5835 {
5836 uint32_t i = 0u;
5837 int32_t wOffset;
5838
5839 /* Copy the value of Index pointer that points
5840 * to the current location where the input samples to be copied */
5841 wOffset = *writeOffset;
5842
5843 /* Loop over the blockSize */
5844 i = blockSize;
5845
5846 while(i > 0u)
5847 {
5848 /* copy the input sample to the circular buffer */
5849 circBuffer[wOffset] = *src;
5850
5851 /* Update the input pointer */
5852 src += srcInc;
5853
5854 /* Circularly update wOffset. Watch out for positive and negative value */
5855 wOffset += bufferInc;
5856 if(wOffset >= L)
5857 wOffset -= L;
5858
5859 /* Decrement the loop counter */
5860 i--;
5861 }
5862
5863 /* Update the index pointer */
5864 *writeOffset = (uint16_t)wOffset;
5865 }

6029 int32_t L,
6030 uint16_t * writeOffset,
6031 int32_t bufferInc,
6032 const q7_t * src,
6033 int32_t srcInc,
6034 uint32_t blockSize)
6035 {
6036 uint32_t i = 0u;
6037 int32_t wOffset;
6038
6039 /* Copy the value of Index pointer that points
6040 * to the current location where the input samples to be copied */
6041 wOffset = *writeOffset;
6042
6043 /* Loop over the blockSize */
6044 i = blockSize;
6045
6046 while(i > 0u)
6047 {
6048 /* copy the input sample to the circular buffer */
6049 circBuffer[wOffset] = *src;
6050
6051 /* Update the input pointer */
6052 src += srcInc;
6053
6054 /* Circularly update wOffset. Watch out for positive and negative value */
6055 wOffset += bufferInc;
6056 if(wOffset >= L)
6057 wOffset -= L;
6058
6059 /* Decrement the loop counter */
6060 i--;
6061 }
6062
6063 /* Update the index pointer */
6064 *writeOffset = (uint16_t)wOffset;
6065 }

6071 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE void arm_circularRead_q7(
6072 q7_t * circBuffer,
6073 int32_t L,
6074 int32_t * readOffset,
6075 int32_t bufferInc,
6076 q7_t * dst,
6077 q7_t * dst_base,
6078 int32_t dst_length,
6079 int32_t dstInc,
6080 uint32_t blockSize)
6081 {
6082 uint32_t i = 0;
6083 int32_t rOffset, dst_end;
6084
6085 /* Copy the value of Index pointer that points
6086 * to the current location from where the input samples to be read */
6087 rOffset = *readOffset;
6088
6089 dst_end = (int32_t) (dst_base + dst_length);
6090
6091 /* Loop over the blockSize */
6092 i = blockSize;
6093
6094 while(i > 0u)
6095 {
6096 /* copy the sample from the circular buffer to the destination buffer */
6097 *dst = circBuffer[rOffset];
6098
6099 /* Update the input pointer */
6100 dst += dstInc;
6101
6102 if(dst == (q7_t *) dst_end)
6103 {
6104 dst = dst_base;
6105 }
6106
6107 /* Circularly update rOffset. Watch out for positive and negative value */
6108 rOffset += bufferInc;
6109
6110 if(rOffset >= L)
6111 {
6112 rOffset -= L;
6113 }
6114
6115 /* Decrement the loop counter */
6116 i--;
6117 }
6118
6119 /* Update the index pointer */
6120 *readOffset = rOffset;
6121 }

6774 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE float32_t arm_bilinear_interp_f32(
6775 const arm_bilinear_interp_instance_f32 * S,
6776 float32_t X,
6777 float32_t Y)
6778 {
6779 float32_t out;
6780 float32_t f00, f01, f10, f11;
6781 float32_t *pData = S->pData;
6782 int32_t xIndex, yIndex, index;
6783 float32_t xdiff, ydiff;
6784 float32_t b1, b2, b3, b4;
6785
6786 xIndex = (int32_t) X;
6787 yIndex = (int32_t) Y;
6788
6789 /* Care taken for table outside boundary */
6790 /* Returns zero output when values are outside table boundary */
6791 if(xIndex < 0 || xIndex > (S->numRows - 1) || yIndex < 0 || yIndex > (S->numCols - 1))
6792 {
6793 return (0);
6794 }
6795
6796 /* Calculation of index for two nearest points in X-direction */
6797 index = (xIndex - 1) + (yIndex - 1) * S->numCols;
6798
6799
6800 /* Read two nearest points in X-direction */
6801 f00 = pData[index];
6802 f01 = pData[index + 1];
6803
6804 /* Calculation of index for two nearest points in Y-direction */
6805 index = (xIndex - 1) + (yIndex) * S->numCols;
6806
6807
6808 /* Read two nearest points in Y-direction */
6809 f10 = pData[index];
6810 f11 = pData[index + 1];
6811
6812 /* Calculation of intermediate values */
6813 b1 = f00;
6814 b2 = f01 - f00;
6815 b3 = f10 - f00;
6816 b4 = f00 - f01 - f10 + f11;
6817
6818 /* Calculation of fractional part in X */
6819 xdiff = X - xIndex;
6820
6821 /* Calculation of fractional part in Y */
6822 ydiff = Y - yIndex;
6823
6824 /* Calculation of bi-linear interpolated output */
6825 out = b1 + b2 * xdiff + b3 * ydiff + b4 * xdiff * ydiff;
6826
6827 /* return to application */
6828 return (out);
6829 }

6840 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE q31_t arm_bilinear_interp_q31(
6841 arm_bilinear_interp_instance_q31 * S,
6842 q31_t X,
6843 q31_t Y)
6844 {
6845 q31_t out; /* Temporary output */
6846 q31_t acc = 0; /* output */
6847 q31_t xfract, yfract; /* X, Y fractional parts */
6848 q31_t x1, x2, y1, y2; /* Nearest output values */
6849 int32_t rI, cI; /* Row and column indices */
6850 q31_t *pYData = S->pData; /* pointer to output table values */
6851 uint32_t nCols = S->numCols; /* num of rows */
6852
6853 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
6854 /* 12 bits for the table index */
6855 /* Index value calculation */
6856 rI = ((X & (q31_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
6857
6858 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
6859 /* 12 bits for the table index */
6860 /* Index value calculation */
6861 cI = ((Y & (q31_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
6862
6863 /* Care taken for table outside boundary */
6864 /* Returns zero output when values are outside table boundary */
6865 if(rI < 0 || rI > (S->numRows - 1) || cI < 0 || cI > (S->numCols - 1))
6866 {
6867 return (0);
6868 }
6869
6870 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
6871 /* shift left xfract by 11 to keep 1.31 format */
6872 xfract = (X & 0x000FFFFF) << 11u;
6873
6874 /* Read two nearest output values from the index */
6875 x1 = pYData[(rI) + (int32_t)nCols * (cI) ];
6876 x2 = pYData[(rI) + (int32_t)nCols * (cI) + 1];
6877
6878 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
6879 /* shift left yfract by 11 to keep 1.31 format */
6880 yfract = (Y & 0x000FFFFF) << 11u;
6881
6882 /* Read two nearest output values from the index */
6883 y1 = pYData[(rI) + (int32_t)nCols * (cI + 1) ];
6884 y2 = pYData[(rI) + (int32_t)nCols * (cI + 1) + 1];
6885
6886 /* Calculation of x1 * (1-xfract ) * (1-yfract) and acc is in 3.29(q29) format */
6887 out = ((q31_t) (((q63_t) x1 * (0x7FFFFFFF - xfract)) >> 32));
6888 acc = ((q31_t) (((q63_t) out * (0x7FFFFFFF - yfract)) >> 32));
6889
6890 /* x2 * (xfract) * (1-yfract) in 3.29(q29) and adding to acc */
6891 out = ((q31_t) ((q63_t) x2 * (0x7FFFFFFF - yfract) >> 32));
6892 acc += ((q31_t) ((q63_t) out * (xfract) >> 32));
6893
6894 /* y1 * (1 - xfract) * (yfract) in 3.29(q29) and adding to acc */
6895 out = ((q31_t) ((q63_t) y1 * (0x7FFFFFFF - xfract) >> 32));
6896 acc += ((q31_t) ((q63_t) out * (yfract) >> 32));
6897
6898 /* y2 * (xfract) * (yfract) in 3.29(q29) and adding to acc */
6899 out = ((q31_t) ((q63_t) y2 * (xfract) >> 32));
6900 acc += ((q31_t) ((q63_t) out * (yfract) >> 32));
6901
6902 /* Convert acc to 1.31(q31) format */
6903 return ((q31_t)(acc << 2));
6904 }

6914 CMSIS_INLINE __STATIC_INLINE q15_t arm_bilinear_interp_q15(
6915 arm_bilinear_interp_instance_q15 * S,
6916 q31_t X,
6917 q31_t Y)
6918 {
6919 q63_t acc = 0; /* output */
6920 q31_t out; /* Temporary output */
6921 q15_t x1, x2, y1, y2; /* Nearest output values */
6922 q31_t xfract, yfract; /* X, Y fractional parts */
6923 int32_t rI, cI; /* Row and column indices */
6924 q15_t *pYData = S->pData; /* pointer to output table values */
6925 uint32_t nCols = S->numCols; /* num of rows */
6926
6927 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
6928 /* 12 bits for the table index */
6929 /* Index value calculation */
6930 rI = ((X & (q31_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
6931
6932 /* Input is in 12.20 format */
6933 /* 12 bits for the table index */
6934 /* Index value calculation */
6935 cI = ((Y & (q31_t)0xFFF00000) >> 20);
6936
6937 /* Care taken for table outside boundary */
6938 /* Returns zero output when values are outside table boundary */
6939 if(rI < 0 || rI > (S->numRows - 1) || cI < 0 || cI > (S->numCols - 1))
6940 {
6941 return (0);
6942 }
6943
6944 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
6945 /* xfract should be in 12.20 format */
6946 xfract = (X & 0x000FFFFF);
6947
6948 /* Read two nearest output values from the index */
6949 x1 = pYData[((uint32_t)rI) + nCols * ((uint32_t)cI) ];
6950 x2 = pYData[((uint32_t)rI) + nCols * ((uint32_t)cI) + 1];
6951
6952 /* 20 bits for the fractional part */
6953 /* yfract should be in 12.20 format */
6954 yfract = (Y & 0x000FFFFF);
6955
6956 /* Read two nearest output values from the index */
6957 y1 = pYData[((uint32_t)rI) + nCols * ((uint32_t)cI + 1) ];
6958 y2 = pYData[((uint32_t)rI) + nCols * ((uint32_t)cI + 1) + 1];
6959
6960 /* Calculation of x1 * (1-xfract ) * (1-yfract) and acc is in 13.51 format */
6961
6962 /* x1 is in 1.15(q15), xfract in 12.20 format and out is in 13.35 format */
6963 /* convert 13.35 to 13.31 by right shifting and out is in 1.31 */
6964 out = (q31_t) (((q63_t) x1 * (0xFFFFF - xfract)) >> 4u);
6965 acc = ((q63_t) out * (0xFFFFF - yfract));
6966
6967 /* x2 * (xfract) * (1-yfract) in 1.51 and adding to acc */
6968 out = (q31_t) (((q63_t) x2 * (0xFFFFF - yfract)) >> 4u);
6969 acc += ((q63_t) out * (xfract));
6970
6971 /* y1 * (1 - xfract) * (yfract) in 1.51 and adding to acc */
6972 out = (q31_t) (((q63_t) y1 * (0xFFFFF - xfract)) >> 4u);
6973 acc += ((q63_t) out * (yfract));
6974
6975 /* y2 * (xfract) * (yfract) in 1.51 and adding to acc */
6976 out = (q31_t) (((q63_t) y2 * (xfract)) >> 4u);
6977 acc += ((q63_t) out * (yfract));
6978
6979 /* acc is in 13.51 format and down shift acc by 36 times */
6980 /* Convert out to 1.15 format */
6981 return ((q15_t)(acc >> 36));
6982 }

6999 q31_t xfract, yfract; /* X, Y fractional parts */

7043 out = ((x2 * (0xFFFFF - yfract)));

7051 out = ((y2 * (yfract)));
